Bug Report for Backend Team: UpdateEvent Validation Too Strict for Status-Only Updates

  Summary

  The updateEvent mutation in the steverhoton-events-handler-prod lambda has overly strict validation rules that require maintenanceDetails for
  any update to maintenance events, even when only updating the status field.

  Error Details

  - Error Type: Lambda validation error
  - Error Message: event validation failed: [(root): Must validate "then" as "if" was valid (root): maintenanceDetails is required (root): Must 
  validate all the schemas (allOf)]
  - Lambda Function: steverhoton-events-handler-prod
  - GraphQL Operation: updateEvent
  - Affected Event Types: Maintenance category events specifically
  - Working Event Types: Fault events (status-only updates work)

  Root Cause Analysis

  The lambda has conditional schema validation (if/then) logic that requires maintenanceDetails whenever updating maintenance events, regardless
  of whether only the status field is being changed.

  Specific Issues:
  1. Overly Strict Conditional Validation: The if/then schema validation triggers when updating maintenance events
  2. Required Field Mismatch: maintenanceDetails is required even for simple status changes
  3. AllOf Schema Logic: All validation schemas must pass, preventing partial updates

  Reproduction Steps

   Working Case (Fault Events):
  mutation {
    updateEvent(input: {
      accountId: "e4c8f468-e0b1-7049-6f0f-48b0b4f27aa5",
      eventId: "eba7e20a-1ef6-4cfa-855e-e75369cb2900",  # brake_fault event
      status: "in_progress"
    }) {
      eventId status
    }
  }
  # Result:  SUCCESS - Updates status successfully

   Failing Case (Maintenance Events):
  mutation {
    updateEvent(input: {
      accountId: "e4c8f468-e0b1-7049-6f0f-48b0b4f27aa5",
      eventId: "defead90-5324-4847-a1cb-bc057171e03f",  # scheduled_service event
      status: "resolved"
    }) {
      eventId status
    }
  }
  # Result:  FAILS - Requires maintenanceDetails

  Secondary Issue: Invalid Status Values

  The error also indicates status validation issues:
  status: status must be one of the following: "created", "acknowledged", "in_progress", "resolved", "closed", "cancelled", "on_hold",
  "escalated"

  The status value "completed" is not in the allowed list, but "resolved" is valid.

  Impact

  - High Priority: Breaks archive functionality in Triage Center
  - Affected Operations: Status updates for maintenance events
  - Working Operations: Status updates for fault events, all other CRUD operations
  - User Experience: Cannot change status of maintenance events without providing unnecessary maintenance details

  Current Validation Logic (Problematic)

  // Current (broken) - Requires maintenanceDetails for ANY maintenance event update
  if (eventCategory === "maintenance") {
    // Validation requires maintenanceDetails even for status-only updates
    required: ["maintenanceDetails"]
  }

  Required Fix

  The lambda validation should allow partial updates when only changing non-category-specific fields like status:

  // Recommended fix - Conditional validation based on fields being updated
  if (eventCategory === "maintenance" &&
      (input.maintenanceDetails || isUpdatingMaintenanceSpecificFields(input))) {
    // Only require maintenanceDetails when actually updating maintenance-specific fields
    required: ["maintenanceDetails"]
  } else {
    // Allow status-only updates without category-specific details
  }

  Suggested Implementation Approaches

  Option 1 (Preferred): Conditional Validation Based on Fields
  // Only enforce category-specific validation when updating category-specific fields
  const isUpdatingMaintenanceFields = input.maintenanceDetails ||
                                     input.scheduledDate ||
                                     input.serviceType;

  if (eventCategory === "maintenance" && isUpdatingMaintenanceFields) {
    // Apply maintenance-specific validation
  }

  Option 2: Separate Update Types
  // Different validation rules for different update types
  if (isStatusOnlyUpdate(input)) {
    // Minimal validation for status changes
  } else if (isFullUpdate(input)) {
    // Full validation including category-specific requirements
  }

  Option 3: Make Category Details Optional for Updates
  // Change schema to make maintenanceDetails optional for updates
  UpdateEventInput: {
    maintenanceDetails: MaintenanceDetailsInput  // Remove required constraint
  }

  Testing Requirements

  After fix implementation:
  1.  Status-only updates work for maintenance events
  2.  Status-only updates continue working for fault events
  3.  Full updates with maintenanceDetails still work
  4.  Validation still prevents invalid status values
  5.  No regression in other update operations

  Valid Status Values for Reference

  "created", "acknowledged", "in_progress", "resolved", 
  "closed", "cancelled", "on_hold", "escalated"

  Event IDs for Testing

  - Maintenance Event: defead90-5324-4847-a1cb-bc057171e03f (scheduled_service)
  - Fault Event: eba7e20a-1ef6-4cfa-855e-e75369cb2900 (brake_fault)

  Priority: High

  This blocks essential Triage Center functionality for changing maintenance event statuses, which is a core workflow for fleet management
  operations.

  The issue is specifically in the lambda validation logic and requires updating the conditional schema validation to allow partial updates for
  status-only changes.

